HEADWORD: Selenocentric
<hw>Se*le`no*cen"tric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>selh`nh</grk> the moon + E. <ets>centric</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>As seen or estimated from the center of the
moon; with the moon central.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

